Rating: 4
Two years later and healthier cooking---here's how I appended the original recipe: Forget the sauce--I know it's great, but you can get the same flavor from (believe it or not) REDUCED fat Hellman's (the latest Cooks says that the Hellman's Canola is great, too)mixed in a much smaller amount into the crab cake itself. I also didn't have celery on hand, so used celery seed, which made for a much less watery cake and still imparted good celery flavor. Continue to use the panko, and if really chilled--forget frying--BROIL. (or cook at really high heat if that isn't an option.) Believe it or not, just as good and maybe even more crab flavor without the competing oil. Also, makes this much easier to serve for hors d'oevers or main course for a dinner party. No last minute frying! This is my best crabcake recipe I've ever tried. My husband wholeheartedly agreed!

