Rating: 4
Used 1 lb. can crabmeat from Costco, 1/2 C. panko crumbs, 1 med. jalapeño, plus other ingredients in the crab cakes. Used another 1/2 C. panko crumbs to dredge, pushing extra crumbs into tops of cakes. They will be hard to hold together, so chill for several hours, then put in the freezer for 10-15 minutes before frying. Then make sure the first side is completely brown before turning (maybe lower heat so they don't brown too fast). I like serving them over baby lettuce or romaine hearts (as recommended by impattyb). Both crab cakes and sauce are spicy, so cool and crunch are good. Leftovers can be reheated (I used the toaster-oven) and are delicious. If you make this recipe with 1/2 lb. crabmeat, use one egg but halve the other ingredients. This makes a generous amount for two.

